<frame name="FR_Attempt_suasion.to_do" ID="10004" xsi:schemaLocation="../schema/frame.xsd" xmlns="http://framenet.icsi.berkeley.edu" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" domains="Cognitive_positions">
    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The  &lt;fen&gt;Persuader&lt;/fen&gt; expresses, through language or otherwise, their wish to get the &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer&lt;/fen&gt; to perform an &lt;fen&gt;Action&lt;/fen&gt; or do something in order to get the &lt;fen&gt;Action&lt;/fen&gt; done. There is no implication that the &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer&lt;/fen&gt; forms an intention to act, let alone acts.
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;

<!--&lt;ex&gt;TODO: SATURER LES VINF DU RÔLE ACTION&lt;/ex&gt;-->

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Persuader"&gt;Mr Smithers&lt;/fex&gt; always &lt;t&gt;encourages&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Add"&gt;the employees&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;fex name="Action"&gt;to stay late and work harder&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Persuader"&gt;Dennis Rodman&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;advises&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Action"&gt;moderation in all things&lt;/fex&gt;. &lt;fex name="Add"&gt;INI&lt;/fex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;asf&gt;Relation to fndata-1.5&lt;/asf&gt; : Results from the splitting of Attempt_suasion into two frames, FR_Attempt_suasion.to_do and  &lt;frframe&gt;FR_Attempt_suasion.content&lt;/frframe&gt;, based on the nature of the &lt;fen&gt;Content&lt;/fen&gt; role (respectively action and mental content). This frame also differs from Attempt_suasion in that the persuading is not necessarily attempted through the use of language.
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
